content: This sequel doesn't improve off the first. Disney's twist villain, story is short, relationships are artificial and flat, villain/all characters are 1 dimensional, more races that act exactly like stereotypes of their archetypes, and actions that do not define your personality but rather your stats. Characters have no development to them, villains are bosses to beat and Legacy Bonus, the cashgrab for a satisfying end, doesn't have content in it, just stats and items. This trilogy isn't worth buy
Fun and good reply but the next one just isn't good and hurt all the great things about this one and the one before it
May i please get a refund rhis wasnt the book i was gonna buy and i barely read it
Great game but it could do a little better with how large and long the story is

I actually purchased this book. Excellent sequel to the masterpiece original. You get to make alliances and wage war. The plot, and the characters were interesting. My favorite part was visiting the different races all over the world. The story even has a twist at the end. Highly recommend.

Much better and emersive than part 1. You have freedom as a leader and strategist and your choices matter. I did not enjoy the pure stat-based strategy when keeping your troops operational, but did not mind it all too much either. As a whole, I would recommend.
Lots of fun and interesting choices to be made. Play over and over as new characters
Definitely expands on the first game in ever more complex ways. Also it gives you far more class based choices which is a great touch.

A bit bummer that there is a particular storyline (about the time traveling wizard) that was added beyond the regular price, but overall the pretty wide range of playthrough in this sequel is so satisfying so I can't complain :'D
LOVED IT
Please release the next one as soon as possible

I have so much fun and I'mm completely invested in the story and characters. Great work on this game. My only gripe (and its a BIG one) is it's inability to delete profiles i dont care about or need or are just stupid duplicates i accidentally created, cluttering up and confusing me. This needs to be fixed!!
the whole series is pretty phenomenal I find these types of apps to be the highest quality form of mobile entertainment and the lost heir is definitely the best I've seen this far
Another 1 of my fav best series
interesting
loved it just can't find the damn dragons
Great fun
Amazing mix of rpg elements and storytelling. The class system is so satisfying. This dev deserves money for their hard work, if you can, invest in this excellent CYOA game-book.
Cool
Story moves faster than the first but I do like it more.
Again, kust wonderful! Thanks so much, Mike Walter : ) Your work has brought me countless hours of joy!

A good sequel, it has all of its predecessor's stengths, and the 
introduction of prestige classes makes this game oh so replayable

I'd love it better if it wasn't almost completely railroaded to a point. 
Great story and it had me feeling things for characters.

I love the diversity in classes but some ending classes are way better then

Jess is the best romance in the game. Her training in the Academy opens up Catalyst, the strongest class in the game.
Amazing story. Super intense and actually challenging
Awesome!
I love it

It ok. The first one was better. This one makes it incredibly hard to get a decent ending. You're army either runs out of food or you're citizens dislike you and you can't get people to join you either way you lose.
Great game. Ive played through 7 times already and im still finding new stories
I'm completely invested in the story and the play and how many actual options they give you.
It worth every penny! Great story!
if there is 6 stars i would have given it! The story is intense can be a bit more dramatic and not cut short sometimes but overall a piece of work to be follow to the end of far reach lands!

I love this series and this one in particular. I was just reading the description of this one and was like, "Wait! Dragons!?" Of course when I played through, I didn't come any dragons, but despite not coming across my favorite fantasy creatures, still a wonderful game.
I hate how I cannot start off where I left off in the first book with my so called email I used to save when I finished the first book and have no choice but to Create new character...
A master piece of the genre have yet to find everything and that level of hard work makes it worth more then five
The game is awesome with so many choices. Definitely not easy though.
Awesome , I'am waiting for lost heir 3. Keep up the good work

Wanted to wait until 3 was out, but thought i'd start 1 and 2 now since 3 will be coming hopefully in February.  Now, the story is definitely rushed -- I would have loved loved loved a longer read, but I understand that'd be a gargantuan task for an interactive novel. I've already gone through a few different paths. Loved it and can't wait for 3! GJ author :).
I've read a lot of choose your own adventure style games on android, and this is my favorite.
Great!
The lost heir series is definitely my favorite interactive story series out there. I can't wait for lost heir 3 to come out. I would rate this a 100/10 if i could

Even better than the first one!!!

From my replays. I think the Prestige class didnt play much role in part 2(of course cause you can only get it when it almost end) But I guess Necromancer is great(if you evil) you can get legendary ride and revive soldier(people wont like it). So I dont think prestige is should be a focus and you could always max normal class to get top of the class achievement. Each has it pros and cons(though I only focus on magic or divine). Other than that each class had few different scene. I had great time replaying
This series is awesome! I have played through so many choices, and I'm still not tired of playing. My biggest question is when will the 3rd installment be ready to play?
This series is definitely one of my favorites
Awesome!!!

Pros: Contains a huge amount of customization opportunities, character development, and true strategic gameplay with reasonable consequences. Cons: It is extremely difficult to to master more than one path, one tactical error can ruin your game (no second chances), and the villians lack significant motives past being evil and power hungry (though this is only part 2 of 3, so more may be revealed). Rating: Nearly Flawless
More like a book but still awesome,  please hurry and make the rest of the story.
Great sequel! Can't wait for the next chapter in my story.
So many choices
By far one of the best interactive choce story base games I have played! My only complaints is I wish it was longer because I enjoy it so much getting to the end makes me a little sad that it's over.

I love the story and I get into it but I stop and think why would you call Karla my friend right after we make the infinity arrow when I gave her a promise ring and our relationship level is 100%. I just feel like it takes away from what could be a really immersive experience.
I loved the game and cannot wait for next part to be released its SO GOOD!! Give it a try, you won't be disappointed!

Love the second part, going around and recruiting different races for war and alone the way to battle your decisions get difficult as you try to make it to the city with minium delay. I lost but I'm looking forward to the third part and to replaying the series again so I can make better decisions.
Really loved it!
Undoubtedly the best novel-based RPG I've ever played. Cannot wait for the sequel!
Love it

I don't know how many hours I've put into this game and I keep coming back. There are so many paths to take, secrets to discover and achievements. I still haven't completed all of them! The writing is fantastic and your choices really matter. Great sequel and I can't wait for the next one!
It's a great story and for cheap too
The wait was WORTH it. This part gives you so many times to improve your skills and the story is a much better improvement compared to the last. And that ending though!
An awesome sequel. It does a great job of carrying over choices from the first game and expanding upon them. Love the story and all of the options.
Love all of this series,  great work guys! Bring on 3!
Cant wait for new chapter
They made me expect dragons
Really good story, but I felt it was far too short for the price I paid. Some of the longer Choice of Games games are the same price and triple the length. But I liked it mostly.

I continue to enjoy playing through this series. It has held my interest now for awhile and I havent become bored. The only reason I did not give 5 stars is that I wish there were a way to delete a character from the list after adding a better one. Keep up the good work Choice Of Games, and "Hats off" to the authors!
I never read a book in my adult life. I couldn't stop reading this......

Amazing

The sheer volume of choices, each casting tiny plot sways which gather to send you to so many places with so many options, the replay value is the highest I've played. Start with Lost Heir 1... there's even a HUGE forum at COG with an ever growing community finding neat little tricks and boosts.
One if the better Choice of Adventure games I've played. Very enjoyable, even for a stock standard fantasy setting (not usually my cup of tea).
Brilliant game :) must play again gotta find out how to ride a dragon ? Is there a dragon? I not been able to encounter one yet :/ ... carnt wait for the next part to the epic story
I have replayed this game 20 times creating different experiences. This is what choosing your own adventure is about.
Can't stop reading it.
Lots of fun, hard choices and memorable characters :) can't wait for part 3
Holy SHAITE! It's out already??!! Can't wait to play thiiiiissss! Will properly review after playing it. For now, cannot contain the glee of seeing the 2nd installment XD
Very Entertaining way better than the first, also it's longer in length, well worth the wait.
Good game
There are many hard decisions to make, I restarted it twice after screwing up badly XD very good read.
I love this chapter in the game is even better than the first one so much stuff to do something choices to make very interesting all round good game can't wait for part 3
The story continues with an even greater range of scenarios that can be played and also has an excellent plot. I look forward to part 3
This is a very well written, gloriously imagined game that continues on well from the first installation!

This author is Bioware in interactive novels. You can be what you want to be and the world recognizes you as such. From saintly to demonic, from warrior to wizard, from skull-breaker to sly politician/seductress. It has it all and on top of it a very heroic story in the best Bioware traditions. Kudos to the author for the excellent job done!
This is easily one of the best mobile games I have ever played and I would recommend it to anyone!!!
Fast paced and we'll written. Excellent follow up to the first.

I really loved this one!!  it is really fun to feel the power..with the armie's at your side the      decisions are very important...so may possibilities !! wish it was even longer!!  it'sa 5 star for me
Great game, just would have preferred some checkpoints. Other than that, excellent.
The game was great
